  <h2>Transferring records from another practice</h2>
  <p>When you register with us, we'll automatically request your medical records from your previous GP practice. You don't need to do anything — we handle this as part of your registration.</p>
  <p>This process can take several weeks. You can still book appointments and receive care from us in the meantime.</p>

  <h2>Viewing your records online</h2>
  <p>Once registered, you can view a summary of your medical records — including your conditions, medications, and allergies — through <a href="{{ site.patientAccess }}" rel="noopener noreferrer">Patient Access</a>.</p>

  <h2>Requesting a copy of your records</h2>
  <p>Under UK data protection law (UK GDPR), you have the right to request a copy of your personal data — including your medical records. This is called a <strong>Subject Access Request (SAR)</strong>.</p>
  <p>To make a SAR, please write to us or email <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a> with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your full name and date of birth</li>
    <li>Your address and contact details</li>
    <li>A description of the records you're requesting</li>
    <li>Proof of identity (a copy of your photo ID)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We must respond within one month of receiving your request. There is no charge for a SAR.</p>

  <h2>Data protection</h2>
  <p>We take the privacy and security of your records very seriously. For more information about how we use your data, please see our <a href="/contact/data-protection/">data protection notice</a>.</p>

</div>
